            <title>[SPARK-54028] Use empty schema when altering a view which is not Hive compatible</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-54028</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spark attempts to save views in a Hive-compatible format and only sets the schema to empty if the save operation fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, due to certain Hive compatibility issues, the save operation may succeed while subsequent read operations fail. This issue arises after the change introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-46934&quot; title=&quot;Read/write roundtrip for struct type with special characters with HMS &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-46934&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-46934&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which removed the &lt;tt&gt;verifyColumnDataType&lt;/tt&gt; check during the &lt;tt&gt;ALTER TABLE&lt;/tt&gt; operation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
